History
What started out as a quick fix turned out to be a compleate rebuild. 
The Origonal problem was that 'sounds' could not be heard by PC's if a dm is invisable... which made the tool useless, and only had 3 visual effects 2 summoning effects.
I started fixxing the sounds and realized, DM's lack a real good tool to aid in DMing. So I compiled every possable use a wand could be and what I could not acomplish ingame that I needed a extra tool for aid.

I still owe and wish to give thanks and reconition to Jhenne and Dopple for the origonal 'fx wand' since it most likely would have never acourd to me to make this, and since most sounds, earthquake, lighting and firestorm were mapped out by them.

Save/Load Functions
Created by: LP
-------------------------------------------
Some functions on the Omega Wand take alot of fine tuning. DM's wishing to use these functions would be able to tune there effects and settings to there percise liking.

But there was a draw back. After server reload or hell exiting the wand, the fine tuning the DM has done vanish.. and he/she must do it all over again from scratch.

Not any more. With the Save/Load functions, a DM can instantly restore his settings, allowing for a more personal Omega Wand, and professional working zone.

<StartAction>[Note:]</Start> Save and Load functions are limited to only a few functions. Once I adopt this to NWNX2 the whole wand will be customizable to your liking.

The Marathon Man
--------------------------------

A function I added to deal with PC's who ALWAYS run, and do it IC. It is not ment for punishment, simply to provide a IC reason to walk. (in actuality it is punishment of a sort. Got to realize I came from ALFA guys :P)

What it does is once you selected a PC, it will give him a fraction of a chance (a 25 roll on tumble) if failed, it will knock them to there knees for 4 seconds and do 2 bludging damage. 
It will also send a server type message to them that they triped wile running, better take it slow.
DISCLAIMER: This only works if a DM uses the Omega tool, and targets the PC. Please use in good taist.

Posion Types
-------------------------------------------
30 + posions.. so it was broken down into lists. Note that some posions can fit two definitions, so I put them in the most logical place.

<StartAction>[Contact: ]</Start> Merely touching this type of poison can posion the target. It can be actively delivered via a weapon or a touch attack. Even if a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison can still affect it. A chest or other object can be smeared with contact poison as part of a trap.

<StartAction>[Ingested: ]</Start> The target must actualy place this posion in it's mouth/eye to become effected. This can happen by spiked potions, or mearly touching the posion and casualy taisting it/rubbing it's eye.

<StartAction>[Inhaled: ]</Start> These posion's are airborn, generly but not always in a posion fog of some kind. Note that holding there breath does little to no good, since they can be absorbed directly though the skin.
Injury

Injury Posions
-------------------------------------------
The Posion must be delivered though an injury of some kind to be effective. If a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison does not affect it. 

Its normaly used in conjuction with a percing attacks, though any contact with an open wound will cause a chance of effection.

Inhaled Posions
-------------------------------------------
 These posion's are airborn, generly but not limited to  a posion fog of some kind. Note that holding there breath does little to no good, since they can be absorbed directly though the skin.

Ingested Posions
-------------------------------------------
The target must actualy place this posion in it's mouth/eye to become effected. This can happen by spiked potions, or mearly touching the posion and casualy taisting it/rubbing your eye.

Contact Posions
-------------------------------------------
Merely handling this type of poison can posion the target. It can be actively delivered via a weapon or a touch attack. Even if a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison can still affect it. A chest or other object can be smeared with contact poison as part of a trap.

Zombie Creep
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Contracted by zombies.

Its a sickness that is contracted by being near or around rotting flesh of a zombie. Create's a deep sickness, where the infected feel weak and nausous.

<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Zombie Creep Disease. First save at a DC of 15. Subsequent saves at a DC of 15. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers DEX by 1D4 and CON by 1D4. Supernatural Effect.

Soldier Shakes
-------------------------------------------
Contract and information unknown.: 

<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Soldier Shakes Disease. First save at a DC of 25. Supernatural Effect. After 24 hours, the diseased will have one of their ability scores lowered by 1 (PERMANERTLY).

Slimy Doom
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Magicly contracted by extreemly powerfull wizards, or acid based magical creatures.

Victim turns into infectious goo from the inside out. Can cause permanent ability drain

<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Slimy Doom Disease. First save at a DC of 14. Subsequent saves at a DC of 14. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers DEX by 1D4. Extraordinary Effect.

Shakes
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Magicaly contracted. It is contagious.

Causes involuntary twitches, tremors, and fits.
<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Shakes Disease. First save at a DC of 13. Subsequent saves at a DC of 13. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers STR by 1D6. Extraordinary Effect.

Red Slaad Eggs
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Contracted by a strong Slaad, generaly but not limited to, a gray Slaad.

Think Alien. Body ace's, infected feels sick. Blister's start to form, as soon as there the size of a baseball they burst open and by some magical way (way Slaad's reproduce) they become fully grown in seconds.

<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Red Slaad Eggs Disease. First save at a DC of 17. Subsequent saves at a DC of 17. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers DEX by 2D6, STR by 2D6, and CON by 2D6. Extraordinary Effect. At the end of the hour incubation period, the diseased target will take 4D6 of magical damage, be knocked down and a Red Slaad will burst forth from them.

Red Ache
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Magicaly contracted. It is contagious.

Skin turns red, bloated, and warm to the touch.
<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Red Ache Disease. First save at a DC of 15. Subsequent saves at a DC of 15. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers STR by 1D6. Extraordinary Effect.

Mummy Rot
-------------------------------------------
<StartAction>[Roleplaying info]</Start>
Spread by mummies. Successful saving throws do not allow the character to recover (though they do prevent damage normally).

Creates a irrataton all over the infected's skin. It's a necromancy effect.. feels as if the skin its self is becoming undead.. though the infected do not loose the ablity to feel the effects.

<StartAction>[Tecnical Info]</Start>
The Mummy Rot Disease. First save at a DC of 20. Subsequent saves at a DC of 20. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers CON by 1D6. Supernatural Effect.

Even if a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison can still affect it. A chest or other object can be smeared with contact poison as part of a trap.

<StartAction>[Ingested: ]</Start> The target must actualy place this posion in it's mouth/eye to become effected. This can happen by spiked potions, or mearly touching the posion and casualy taisting it/rubbing it's eye.

<StartAction>[Inhaled: ]</Start> These posion's are airborn, generly but not always in a posion fog of some kind. Note that holding there breath does little to no good, since they can be absorbed directly though the skin.
Injury

Injury Posions
-------------------------------------------
The Posion must be delivered though an injury of some kind to be effective. If a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison does not affect it. 

Its normaly used in conjuction with a percing attacks, though any contact with an open wound will cause a chance of effection.

Inhaled Posions
-------------------------------------------
 These posion's are airborn, generly but not limited to  a posion fog of some kind. Note that holding there breath does little to no good, since they can be absorbed directly though the skin.

Ingested Posions
-------------------------------------------
The target must actualy place this posion in it's mouth/eye to become effected. This can happen by spiked potions, or mearly touching the posion and casualy taisting it/rubbing your eye.

Contact Posions
-------------------------------------------
Merely handling this type of poison can posion the target. It can be actively delivered via a weapon or a touch attack. Even if a creature has sufficient damage reduction to avoid taking any damage from the attack, the poison can still affect it. A chest or other object can be smeared with contact poison as part of a trap.

Contracted by zombies.

Its a sickness that is contracted by being near or around rotting flesh of a zombie. Create's a deep sickness, where the infected feel weak and nausous.

The Zombie Creep Disease. First save at a DC of 15. Subsequent saves at a DC of 15. Incubates for 1 hour then lowers DEX by 1D4 and CON by 1D4. Supernatural Effect.

Save/Load Functions
Created by: LP
-------------------------------------------
Some functions on the Omega Wand take alot of fine tuning. DM's wishing to use these functions would be able to tune there effects and settings to there percise liking.

But there was a draw back. After server reload or hell exiting the wand, the fine tuning the DM has done vanish.. and he/she must do it all over again from scratch.

Not any more. With the Save/Load functions, a DM can instantly restore his settings, allowing for a more personal Omega Wand, and professional working zone.

<StartAction>[Note:]</Start> Save and Load functions are limited to only a few functions. Once I adopt this to NWNX2 the whole wand will be customizable to your liking.

The Marathon Man
--------------------------------

A function I added to deal with PC's who ALWAYS run, and do it IC. It is not ment for punishment, simply to provide a IC reason to walk.

What it does is once you selected a PC, it will give him a fraction of a chance (a 25 roll on tumble) if failed, it will knock them to there knees for 4 seconds and do 2 bludging damage. 
It will also send a server type message to them that they triped wile running, better take it slow.
DISCLAIMER: This only works if a DM uses the Omega tool, and targets the PC. Please use in good taist.
